definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.46; 
 son of: Caleb (H3612H) and Ephah (H5891H); 
 brother of: Moza (H4162) and Gazez (H1495); 
 half-brother of: Hur (H2354), Jesher (H3475), Shobab (H7727H), Ardon (H0715), Mareshah@1Ch.2.42 (H4337), Jahdai (H3056), Sheber (H7669), Tirhanah (H8647), Shaaph (H8174H), Sheva (H7724) and Achsah (H5915H); 
 father of: Gazez (H1495H)
 § Haran = "mountaineer"
 a son of Caleb by his concubine Ephah
